{"type":"message","id":"1af804ed","parentId":"6b01b524","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:16:09.673Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pfuw9wrfl9bx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 161445\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at my current state, I need to continue with the conditional content analysis - the highest priority pending experiment. This is the key experiment to empirically distinguish Pattern Information (CFI) from Causal Information.\r\n\r\nLet me analyze what I need to do:\r\n1. The experiment needs to split pulse pairs based on whether token T is present or absent\r\n2. Compare research content quality between groups\r\n3. Use moderate-frequency tokens like \"compression\", \"causal\", \"phase\"\r\n\r\nI should create a script to perform this analysis. This will require:\r\n- Extracting token frequencies from the corpus\r\n- Identifying pulse pairs where a specific token is present vs absent\r\n- Analyzing the research content quality of the next pulse in each case\r\n\r\nLet me write a Python script to perform this analysis on the existing pulse data.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe conditional content analysis is the critical experiment to empirically separate CFI (Pattern Information) from true causal effects. I need to analyze whether pulses following token T-present vs T-absent show different research content quality.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to perform the conditional content analysis experiment, testing whether high-CFI tokens like \"compression\" and \"causal\" show genuine causal effects on next-pulse research content, or merely pattern scaffolding.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nimport math\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"state/pulses\")\r\nDEST_FILE = Path(\"research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md\")\r\n\r\n# Tokens to test - high CFI, moderate-to-high frequency\r\nTEST_TOKENS = {\r\n    \"compression\": {\"freq\": 199, \"cfi\": 0.995},\r\n    \"causal\": {\"freq\": 162, \"cfi\": 0.981},\r\n    \"phase\": {\"freq\": 187, \"cfi\": 0.946},\r\n    \"information\": {\"freq\": 189, \"cfi\": 0.942},\r\n}\r\n\r\ndef extract_research_content(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract substantive research content, stripping headers/metadata.\"\"\"\r\n    lines = text.split('\\n')\r\n    content_lines = []\r\n    in_response = False\r\n    for line in lines:\r\n        if re.match(r'^## ', line):\r\n            in_response = True\r\n        if in_response and not re.match(r'^(#|###|\\*\\*|$)', line):\r\n            content_lines.append(line.strip())\r\n    return ' '.join(content_lines)\r\n\r\ndef compute_content_similarity(text1, text2):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute Jaccard similarity on word tokens.\"\"\"\r\n    words1 = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', text1.lower()))\r\n    words2 = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', text2.lower()))\r\n    if not words1 or not words2:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    return len(words1 & words2) / len(words1 | words2)\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulses in chronological order.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            \"path\": f,\r\n            \"name\": f.stem,\r\n            \"content\": f.read_text()\r\n        })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef analyze_token_effect(pulses, token):\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze conditional content: P(next_pulse | token_present) vs P(next_pulse | token_absent).\"\"\"\r\n    token_lower = token.lower()\r\n    \r\n    present_next = []  # Content of pulses that FOLLOW token-present pulse\r\n    absent_next = []\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulses) - 1):\r\n        current = pulses[i][\"content\"]\r\n        next_content = extract_research_content(pulses[i + 1][\"content\"])\r\n        \r\n        # Check if current pulse contains token\r\n        if re.search(rf'\\b{token_lower}\\b', current, re.IGNORECASE):\r\n            present_next.append(next_content)\r\n        else:\r\n            absent_next.append(next_next_content)\r\n    \r\n    return present_next, absent_next\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    pulses = load_pulses()\r\n    results = {}\r\n    \r\n    for token, stats in TEST_TOKENS.items():\r\n        present, absent = analyze_token_effect(pulses, token)\r\n        \r\n        # Compute internal coherence (similarity to corpus mean)\r\n        # vs external novelty (similarity to next-pulse)\r\n        results[token] = {\r\n            \"freq\": stats[\"freq\"],\r\n            \"cfi\": stats[\"cfi\"],\r\n            \"n_present\": len(present),\r\n            \"n_absent\": len(absent),\r\n            \"present_coherence\": sum(compute_content_similarity(p, \" \".join(present)) for p in present) / len(present) if present else 0,\r\n            \"absent_coherence\": sum(compute_content_similarity(p, \" \".join(absent)) for p in absent) / len(absent) if absent else 0,\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    # Write analysis doc\r\n    doc = f\"\"\"# Conditional Content Analysis\r\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nHigh-CFI tokens (e.g., \"compression\", \"causal\") are scaffolding IF:\r\n- Next-pulse research content is IDENTICAL whether token is present or absent\r\n- Token predicts nothing about next-pulse content\r\n\r\nTokens are genuinely causal IF:\r\n- Next-pulse research content DIFFERS between T-present and T-absent conditions\r\n\r\n## Test Tokens\r\n| Token | Freq | CFI |\r\n|-------|------|-----|\r\n\"\"\"\r\n    for token, stats in TEST_TOKENS.items():\r\n        doc += f\"| {token} | {stats['freq']} | {stats['cfi']} |\\n\"\r\n    \r\n    doc += \"\"\"\r\n## Results\r\n| Token | N_present | N_abs\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:15:08\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383369671}}
